    <statement><p>Simplify the following expression, and if applicable, write the restricted domain on the simplified expression.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{-3x}{x^{2}+3x}}=}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{3}{x+3}, x\ne 0</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cross out common factors:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{-3x}{x^{2}+3x}} \amp = \frac{{-3x}}{{x\mathopen{}\left(x+3\right)}} \\
                     \amp = {-\frac{3}{x+3}, x\ne 0}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>x</m> was crossed out, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>x \ne 0</m>.</p>
</solution>
